uiltiest of pleasures evoke. Zibrak reexamines documents of femme culture long dismissed as “trash” to reveal the surprisingly cathartic experiences produced by tales of domination, privilege, and the material trappings of the heteropatriarchy.Part of the Avidly Reads series, this slim book gives us a new way of looking at American culture. With the singular blend of personal memoir and cultural criticism featured in the series, Avidly Reads Guilty Pleasures reclaims women’s experiences for themselves.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aPopular literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aRomance fictionxHistory and criticism. 0aRomance filmsxHistory and criticism. 0aWomen and literature. 0aWomen in literature. 0aWomenxBooks and reading. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Women's Studies.2bisacsh  aAesthetic Theory.  aAutobiography.  aCritical Race Studies.  aCultural Criticism.  aDivorce.  aFeminism.  aFilm Studies.  aGender Studies.  aGuilt.  aLove.  aMemoir.  aPandemic.  aPeriodical Studies.  aPopular Culture.  aPopular Women Writers.  aPrint Culture.  aQueer Theory.  aRace Studies.  aRomance Novels.  aSentimental Fiction.  aSexuality Studies.  aShame.  aTelevision Studies.  aWhite Privilege.  aWomen’s Culture.  aWomen’s Fiction.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishz978311075418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z97831107391070 cprintz978147980707940u